articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: A surface-to-surface missile fired at central Israel from Yemen hit an unpopulated area, causing no injuries, Israel's military said on Sunday.
articles.title: Missile fired from Yemen set off sirens in central Israel, military says

articles.author: David W Cerny, Marek Strzelecki
articles.description: One person drowned in southwest Poland and thousands were evacuated across the border in the Czech Republic after heavy rain continued to batter central Europe on Sunday, causing flooding in several parts of the region.
articles.title: Floods claim two more casualties as torrential rain batters central Europe

articles.author: Ruma Paul
articles.description: The United States is committed to supporting Bangladesh's inclusive economic growth, institution building and development and will provide an additional $202 million of aid, a U.S. delegation said during a visit to Dhaka on Sunday.
articles.title: US to give Bangladesh $202 million more in aid

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Jordan's Prime Minister Bisher Khasawneh submitted his resignation on Sunday, officials familiar with the matter said, less than week after a parliamentary election that saw some gains for the Islamist opposition in the U.S.-allied kingdom.
articles.title: Jordan prime minister submits resignation days after election, sources say

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Eight people have died trying to cross the Channel from France to England, French authorities said on Sunday, confirming earlier media reports.
articles.title: Eight die in Channel crossing attempt, French authorities say

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Iran's President Masoud Pezeshkian will attend the upcoming BRICS summit in Russia, state media cited Tehran's ambassador in Moscow as saying on Sunday, amid tensions with the West over military cooperation between the two countries.
articles.title: Iran's President to attend BRICS summit in Russia

articles.author: Ju-Min Park, Josh Smith
articles.description: Photos of North Korea's its uranium enrichment facility may show an undeclared site for building nuclear bombs just outside of its capital, analysts said.
articles.title: Photos likely show undeclared North Korea uranium enrichment site, analysts say

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Shanghai halted transportation links, recalled ships and shut tourism spots including Shanghai Disney Resort on Sunday as it braced for Typhoon Bebinca, in what could be the strongest tropical cyclone to hit the Chinese financial hub since 1949.
articles.title: Shanghai braces for direct hit from Typhoon Bebinca

articles.author: Subrata Nag Choudhary
articles.description: India's federal police have charged the former head of R.G. Kar Medical College in Kolkata with tampering with evidence linked to the rape and murder of a junior female doctor, a case that triggered weeks of nationwide protests.
articles.title: Ex-head of India's RG Kar College charged for alleged evidence tampering in rape case

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Two Spanish nationals arrested in Venezuela had no links to the Spanish secret service and Spain was not involved in any plan to politically destabilize the South American country, a Spanish foreign ministry source said on Sunday.
articles.title: Two Spanish nationals arrested in Venezuela not linked to any plot to destabilise country, says Madrid
